hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 RULES\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s54\\qj \\li0\\ri0\\sa100\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\r\n\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 The definition for a rule is provided for under A.R.S. \\'a7\\loch\\f0  41-1001. }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ai\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs114\\i\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \r\n\\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\lquote \\loch\\f0 Rule\\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\rquote \\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 \r\n means an agency statement of general applicability that implements, interprets, or prescribes law or policy, or describes the procedures or practice requirements of an agency.\\'94\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 The }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ai\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs114\\i\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Code}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0  is separated by subject into Titles. Titles are divided into Chapter\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 \r\ns. A Chapter includes state agency rules. Rules in Chapters are divided into Articles, then Sections. The \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 R\\'94\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0  stands for \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 rule\\'94\\loch\\f0 \r\n with a sequential numbering and lettering outline separated into subsections.\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Rules are codified quarterly in the }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ai\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs114\\i\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Code}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 . Suppleme\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 nt release dates are printed on the footers of each Chapter.\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s82\\qj \\li0\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\r\n\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 First Quarter: January 1 - March 31\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Second Quarter: April 1 - June 30\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Third Quarter: July 1 - September 30\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s54\\qj \\li0\\ri0\\sa100\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\r\n\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Fourth Quarter: October 1 - December 31\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 For example, the first supplement for the first \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nquarter of 2022 is cited as Supp. 22-1. Supplements are traditionally released three to four weeks after the end of the quarter because filings are accepted until the last day of the quarter.\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Please note: The Office publishes by Chapter, not by individual \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nrule Section. Therefore there might be only a few Sections codified in each Chapter released in a supplement. This is why the Office lists only updated codified Sections on the previous page.\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s27\\ql \\li0\\ri0\\sl220\\slmult0\\nowidctlpar\\tx720\\tx1440\\tx2160\\tx2880\\tx3600\\tx4320\\tx5040\\tx5760\\tx6480\\tx7200\\tx7920\\tx8640\\wrapdefault\\hyphpar0\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 RULE HISTORY\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s54\\qj \\li0\\ri0\\sa100\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\r\n\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Refer to the HISTORICAL NOTE at the end of each Sec\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 tion for the effective date of a rule. The note also includes the }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \r\n\\ai\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs114\\i\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Register}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\n volume and page number in which the notice was published (A.A.R.) and beginning in supplement 21-4, the date the notice was published in the }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ai\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs114\\i\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Register}\r\n{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 .\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s27\\ql \\li0\\ri0\\sl220\\slmult0\\nowidctlpar\\tx720\\tx1440\\tx2160\\tx2880\\tx3600\\tx4320\\tx5040\\tx5760\\tx6480\\tx7200\\tx7920\\tx8640\\wrapdefault\\hyphpar0\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\