s18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 R18-4-101.\\tab Authority and Purpose\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s59\\qj \\fi-360\\li360\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx360\\tx720\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin360\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 A.\\tab }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 This Chapter is created under the authority of A.R.S. Title 49, Chapter 2, Article 9, and the federal Safe Drinking Water Act, 42 U.S.C. 300f through 300j-26.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 B.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 The purposes of this Chapter include the following:\r\n\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s62\\qj \\fi-360\\li720\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx720\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin720\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 1.\\tab To protect the public health and welfar\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\ne by ensuring that all potable water distributed or sold to the public by public water systems is free from unwholesome, poisonous, deleterious, or other foreign substances, and filth or disease-causing substances or organisms; and\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 2.\\tab To enable the state t\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 o maintain primary enforcement responsibility of the Safe Drinking Water Act, including the requirements of 40 CFR 141 and 142.\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s34\\qc \\li0\\ri0\\sb100\\sl200\\slmult0\\keepn\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Historical Note\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s35\\qc \\fi-360\\li360\\ri360\\sa100\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin360\\lin360\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nFormer Section R9-20-504 repealed, new Section R9-20-504 adopted effective November 1, 1979 (Supp. 79-6). Former\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\n Section R9-20-504 amended, renumbered as Section R9-20-501, then renumbered as Section R18-4-101 effective October 23, 1987 (Supp. 87-4). R18-4-101 recodified to R18-5-101 (Supp. 95-2). New Section adopted effective April 28, 1995 (Supp. 95-2). Amended e\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 f\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nfective June 3, 1998 (Supp. 98-3). Amended effective December 8, 1998 (Supp. 98-4). Amended by final rulemaking effective September 23, 1999; the A.A.R. citation was not available at the time of publication and will appear in Supp. 99-4 (Supp. 99-3). Amen\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 d\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\ned by final rulemaking at 5 A.A.R. 4456, effective September 23, 1999 (Supp. 99-4). Amended by final rulemaking at 8 A.A.R. 973, effective February 19, 2002 (Supp. 02-1). Amended by final rulemaking at 8 A.A.R. 3046, effective May 1, 2002 (Supp. 02-3). Se\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 c\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 tion repealed; new Section made by final rulemaking at 14 A.A.R. 2978, effective August 30, 2008 (Supp. 08-3).\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s15\\qj \\li0\\ri0\\sb120\\sl200\\slmult0\\nowidctlpar\\tx1180\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 R18-4-102.\\tab \r\nIncorporation by Reference of 40 CFR 141 and 142\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s59\\qj \\fi-360\\li360\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx360\\tx720\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin360\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 A.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Unless otherwise specified in this Chapter, all references to regulations in 40 CF\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nR 141 and 142 in this Chapter refer to the July 1, 2014, version of the regulations. Copies of the incorporated material are available for review at the Arizona Department of Environmental Quality, 1110 W. Washington St., Phoenix, AZ, 85007, and are avail\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 a\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 ble from\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0  the U.S. General Printing office at http://www.gpo.gov/fdsys/browse/collectionCfr.action?collectionCode=CFR.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 B.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nA reference to a federal statute or regulation in a federal statute or regulation incorporated by reference in this Chapter shall refe\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nr to and incorporate by reference the referenced statute or regulation as of the date specified in subsection (A), unless the referenced statute or regulation is incorporated by reference elsewhere in this Chapter in a modified form, in which case the ref\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 e\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 rence shall be to the statute or regulation as incorporated in this Chapter.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 C.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nDocuments incorporated by reference in a federal statute or regulation incorporated by reference in this Chapter are also incorporated by reference in this Chapter, as of the date specified in the federal statute or regulation.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 D.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 A federal rule incorporat\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\n\\hich\\f0 ed by reference in this Chapter shall include all \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Effective Date Notes\\'94\\loch\\f0  associated with the federal rule.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 E.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 The term \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 State\\'94\r\n\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0  or \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 primacy agency\\'94\\loch\\f0  in the text of a federal statute or regulation incorporated by reference in this Chapter shall mean the Arizo\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nna Department of Environmental Quality unless otherwise noted.\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s34\\qc \\li0\\ri0\\sb100\\sl200\\slmult0\\keepn\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Historical Note\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s35\\qc \\fi-360\\li360\\ri360\\sa100\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin360\\lin360\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nAdopted as Section R9-20-502 and renumbered as Section R18-4-102 effective October 23, 1987 (Supp. 87-4). R18-4-102 recodified to R18-5-102 (Supp. 95-2). New Section adopted eff\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nective April 28, 1995 (Supp. 95-2). Amended effective June 3, 1998 (Supp. 98-3). Amended by final rulemaking at 8 A.A.R. 973, effective February 19, 2002 (Supp. 02-1). Section repealed; new Section made by final rulemaking at 14 A.A.R. 2978, effective Aug\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 u\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 st 30, 2008 (Supp. 08-3). Amended by final rulemaking at 22 A.A.R. 379, effective April 2, 2016 (Supp. 16-1).\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s15\\qj \\li0\\ri0\\sb120\\sl200\\slmult0\\nowidctlpar\\tx1180\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 R18-4-103.\\tab General \\hich\\f0 \\endash \\loch\\f0 \r\n 40 CFR 141, Subpart A\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s59\\qj \\fi-360\\li360\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx360\\tx720\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin360\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 A.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 40 CFR 141, Subpart A (40 CFR 141.1 through 141.6), is incorporated by reference as of the date spec\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nified in R18-4-102, except for the changes listed in this Section; this incorporation does not include any later amendments or editions.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 B.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 The definition of \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 State\r\n\\'94\\loch\\f0  in 40 CFR 141.2 is not incorporated by reference. In addition to the terms defined in A.R.\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 S. \\'a7\\'a7\\loch\\f0 \r\n 49-201 and 49-351, and 40 CFR 141.2, in this Chapter, unless otherwise specified, the terms listed below have the following meanings.\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s63\\qj \\fi-360\\li720\\ri0\\sa100\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx720\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin720\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Air-gap separation\\'94\\loch\\f0 \r\n means a physical separation between the discharge end of a supply pipe and the top rim of its \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 receiving vessel of at least 1 inch or twice the diameter of the supply pipe, whichever is greater.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 ANSI/NSF Standard 60\\'94\\loch\\f0  means American National Standards Institute/NSF International Standard 60 - 2014a, Drinking Water Treatment Chemicals - Health Effec\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nts, November 17, 2014, incorporated by reference and on file with the Department. This material is available from NSF International, 789 N. Dixboro Road, P.O. Box 130140, Ann Arbor, MI 48113-0140, USA; (734) 769-8010; http://www.nsf.org. This incorporatio\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0  by reference includes no future editions or amendments. \r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 ANSI/NSF Standard 61\\'94\\loch\\f0 \r\n means American National Standards Institute/NSF International Standard 61 - 2014a, Drinking Water System Components - Health Effects, October 19, 2014, incorporated by refere\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nnce and on file with the Department. This material is available from NSF International, 789 N. Dixboro Road, P.O. Box 130140, Ann Arbor, MI 48113-0140, USA; (734) 769-8010; http://www.nsf.org. This incorporation by reference includes no future editions or\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0  \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 amendments.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Backflow\\'94\\loch\\f0 \r\n means a reverse flow condition that causes water or mixtures of water and other liquids, gases, or substances to flow back into the distribution system. Backflow can be created by a difference in water pressure (backpressure), a vac\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 uum or partial vacuum (backsiphonage), or a combination of both.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Backflow-prevention assembly\\'94\\loch\\f0  means a mechanical device used to prevent backflow.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Capacity\\'94\\loch\\f0  means the overall capability of a water system to consistently produce and deliver water meetin\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\ng all national and state primary drinking water regulations in effect when new or modified operations begin. Capacity includes the technical, managerial, and financial capacities of the water system to plan for, achieve, and maintain compliance with appli\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 c\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 able national and state primary drinking water regulations.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Capacity development\\'94\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\n means improving public water system finances, management, infrastructure, and operations, so that the public water system can provide safe drinking water consistently, reliably, and cost-effectively.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Capacity development report\\'94\\loch\\f0  means an annual report a\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\ndopted by the Department that describes progress made in improving technical, managerial, or financial capacity of public water systems in Arizona.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Cross connection\\'94\\loch\\f0  means a physical connection between a public water system and any source of water or oth\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\ner substance that may lead to contamination of the water provided by the public water system through backflow.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Distribution system\\'94\\loch\\f0  means a pipeline, appurtenance, device, and facility of a public water system that conducts water from a source or water t\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nreatment plant to persons served by the system.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Department\\'94\\loch\\f0  means the Arizona Department of Environmental Quality.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Double check valve assembly\\'94\\loch\\f0  means a backflow-prevention assembly that contains two independently acting check valves with tightly closin\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\ng, resilient-seated shut-off valves on each end of the assembly and properly located, resilient-seated test cocks.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Elementary business plan\\'94\\loch\\f0  means a document containing all of the items necessary for a complete review of the technical, managerial, and fi\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nnancial capacity of a new public water system under Article 6 of this Chapter.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Entry point to the distribution system\\'94\\loch\\f0  means a compliance sampling point anywhere on a finished water line that is representative of a water source and located after the well\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\n, surface water intake, treatment plant, storage tank, or pressure tank, whichever is last in the process flow, but prior to where the water is discharged into the distribution system and prior to the first service connection.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 EPA\\'94\\loch\\f0  means the United State\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 s Environmental Protection Agency.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Exclusion\\'94\\loch\\f0  means a waiver granted by the Department under R18-4-219 from a requirement of this Chapter that is not a requirement contained in a federal drinking water law.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Exemption\\'94\\loch\\f0  means a form of temporary relief f\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nrom a maximum contaminant level or treatment technique granted by the Department to a public water system, pending installation and operation of treatment facilities, acquisition of an alternate source, or completion of improvements in treatment processes\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0  \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 to bring the system into compliance with drinking water regulations.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Financial capacity\\'94\\loch\\f0  means the ability of a public water system to acquire and manage sufficient financial resources for the system to achieve and maintain compliance with the federal Sa\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 fe Drinking Water Act.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Groundwater system\\'94\\loch\\f0  means a public water system that is supplied solely by groundwater that is not under the direct influence of surface water.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Lead-free\\'94\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0  has the same meaning prescribed in A.R.S. \\'a7\\loch\\f0  49-353(B).\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 Major stockholder\\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'94\\loch\\f0  means a person who has 20% or more ownership interest in a public water system.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Master priority list\\'94\\loch\\f0  means a list created by the Department that ranks public water systems according to the criteria in R18-4-803.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Monitoring assistance program\\'94\\loch\\f0  means \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 the program established by A.R.S. \\'a7\\loch\\f0 \r\n 49-360 to assist public water systems with mandatory monitoring for contaminants and administered by the Department under 18 A.A.C. 4.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Operational assistance\\'94\\loch\\f0  means professional or financial assistance provided to a pu\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nblic water system to improve the technical, managerial, or financial operations of the public water system.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Protected water source\\'94\\loch\\f0  means a groundwater source that:\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s113\\qj \\fi-360\\li1440\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin1440\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\bullet \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Meets the requirements of A.A.C. R18-5-502(D);\r\n\r\n\\par \\bullet \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Is not located within 100 feet of a dr\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 ywell as defined by A.R.S. \\'a7\\loch\\f0  49-331(3), and\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s25\\qj \\fi-360\\li1440\\ri0\\sa100\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin1440\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\bullet \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 \r\nIs not located within 100 feet of a condition that can constitute an environmental nuisance as described in A.R.S. \\'a7\\loch\\f0  49-141(A).\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s63\\qj \\fi-360\\li720\\ri0\\sa100\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx720\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin720\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 \r\nReduced pressure principle backflow-prevention assembly\\'94\\loch\\f0  means a backflow-preven\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\ntion assembly that contains two independently acting check valves; a hydraulically operating, mechanically independent pressure differential relief valve located between the two check valves; tightly closing, resilient seated shut-off valves on each end o\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 f\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0  the check valve assembly; and properly located resilient seated test cocks.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Service connection\\'94\\loch\\f0  means a location at the meter or, in the absence of a meter, at the curbstop or building inlet.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Service line\\'94\\loch\\f0  means the water line that runs from the corpo\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nration stop at a water main to the building inlet, including any pigtail, gooseneck, or fitting.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 State\\'94\\loch\\f0  means the Arizona Department of Environmental Quality, except during any time period during which the Department does not have primary enforcement res\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 ponsibility pursuant to Section 1413 of the Act, the term \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 State\\'94\\loch\\f0  means the Regional Administrator of EPA Region 9.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 System evaluation assistance\\'94\\loch\\f0  means assistance provided to assess the status of the public water system's technical, managerial, and finan\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\ncial components, with emphasis on infrastructure status.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Technical assistance\\'94\\loch\\f0  means operational assistance, system evaluation assistance, or both.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Treatment\\'94\\loch\\f0  means a process that changes the quality of water by physical, chemical, or biological means.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Treatment technique\\'94\\loch\\f0  means a treatment procedure promulgated by EPA in lieu of an MCL.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Variance\\'94\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\n means relief from a maximum contaminant level or treatment technique granted by the Department to a public water system when characteristics of a system's raw water source preclude the system from complying with maximum contaminant levels prescribed by d\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 r\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 inking water regulations, despite application of best technology, treatment techniques, or other means available to the system.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Water main\\'94\\loch\\f0  means a pipe that is exterior to buildings and is used to distribute drinking water to more than one property.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 W\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 ater Infrastructure Finance Authority\\'94\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0  means the entity created under A.R.S. \\'a7\\loch\\f0 \r\n 49-1201 et seq. to provide financial assistance to political subdivisions, Indian tribes, and eligible drinking water facilities for constructing, acquiring, or improving waste\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 w\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nater treatment facilities, drinking water facilities, nonpoint source projects, and other related water quality facilities and projects.\r\n\\par \\tab \\loch\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\hich\\f0 \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Water treatment plant\\'94\\loch\\f0  means a process, device, or structure used to improve the physical, chemical, or biological qu\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nality of the water in a public water system. A booster chlorination facility that is designed to maintain an effective disinfectant residual in water in the distribution system is not a water treatment plant.\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s59\\qj \\fi-360\\li360\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx360\\tx720\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin360\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 C.\\tab }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 40 CFR 141.4, entitled \\'93\\loch\\f0 variances and exempt\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 ions,\\'94\\loch\\f0  is incorporated by reference subject to the following modifications:\r\n\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s62\\qj \\fi-360\\li720\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx720\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin720\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 1.\\tab \\hich\\f0 The phrase \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 \r\nentity with primary enforcement responsibility\\'94\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0  is changed to \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Department.\\'94\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 2.\\tab When reviewing and acting on requests for variances and exemptions, the Department sha\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 \r\nll act in accordance with the procedures at 42 U.S.C. 300g-4 and 300g-5 (2004) of the Act (Public Health Service Act \\'a7\\'a7\\loch\\f0  1415 and 1416), including:\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s36\\qj \\fi-360\\li1080\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin1080\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 a.\\tab \r\nThe Department shall require a public water system granted a variance under subsection (C) to comply with \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 the requirements in a compliance schedule as expeditiously as practicable.\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 b.\\tab The Department shall promptly notify EPA of all variances and exemptions granted by the Department in the manner specified in the Act.\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 c.\\tab The Department shall enforce a schedule \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 or other requirement on which a variance or exemption is conditioned under 42 U.S.C. 300g-3 and A.R.S. \\'a7\\loch\\f0 \r\n 49-354, as if the schedule or other requirement is part of a national primary drinking water regulation incorporated by reference in this Chapter.\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 d.\\tab \\hich\\f0 \\'93\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Treatment technique requirement,\\'94\\loch\\f0 \r\n for the purpose of subsection (C), means a requirement in a national primary drinking water regulation which specifies for a contaminant, in accordance with 42 U.S.C. 300f(1)(C)(ii), each treatment technique known to lead\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0  \r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 to a reduction in the level of the contaminant sufficient to satisfy the requirements of 42 U.S.C. 300g-1(b).\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 e.\\tab If the Department grants a variance or exemption, the Department shall prescribe:\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s113\\qj \\fi-360\\li1440\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin1440\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 i.\\tab \r\nA compliance schedule that includes increments of progress\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0  or measures to develop an alternative source of water supply; and\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 ii.\\tab An implementation schedule that includes such control measures as the Department deems necessary for each contaminant.\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s59\\qj \\fi-360\\li360\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx360\\tx720\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin360\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 D.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 40 CFR 142, 142.2, 142.20, and Subparts E, F, G, and K, are inc\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\norporated by reference as of the date specified in R18-4-102, with the following changes; this incorporation does not include any later amendments or editions. The following substitutions are to be applied in the listed order.\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s62\\qj \\fi-360\\li720\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx720\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin720\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 1.\\tab 40 CFR 142.46, 142.302, 14\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 2.313 are not incorporated by reference.\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 2.\\tab \\hich\\f0 40 CFR 142.20(a), (b). The phrase \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 States with primary enforcement responsibility\\'94\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0  is changed to \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 the Department\\'94\\loch\\f0 \r\n; the second sentences in 142.20(a) and 142.20(b) are deleted.\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 3.\\tab 40 CFR 142.60(b), 142.61(b). The \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 phrase \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 \r\nAdministrator in a state that does not have primary enforcement responsibility or a state with primary enforcement responsibility (primacy state) that issues variances\\'94\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0  is changed to \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Department.\\'94\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 4.\\tab 40 CFR 142.40(a), (b); 142.41; 142.50(a); 142.51\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 . The phrase \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 a State that does not have primary enforcement responsibility\\'94\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 \r\n is changed to \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Arizona\\'94.\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 5.\\tab \\hich\\f0 40 CFR 142.60(b), (c), (d); 142.61(b), (c). The phrase \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Administrator or [`primacy' or `primary'] state that issues variances\\'94\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0  is changed to \\'93\\loch\\f0 Departmen\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 t.\\'94\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 6.\\tab \\hich\\f0 40 CFR 142.60(b), (d); 142.61(b), (d); 142.62(e), (g)(1); 142.65(a)(4). The phrase \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Administrator or [the] primacy state\\'94\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0  is changed to \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 \r\nDepartmen