ect to the modifications specified in this Section; this incorporation does not include any later amendments or editions.\r\n\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 B.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 4\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\n0 CFR 141.21(c)(2), 141.21(d) and 141.21(f) are not incorporated by reference.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 C.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 \r\n40 CFR 141.22: the last sentence of 141.22(a) is replaced by the following: \\'93\\loch\\f0 Turbidity measurements shall be made using analytical methods approved by EPA and the Arizona Dep\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 artment of Health Services.\r\n\\'94\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 D.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 40 CFR 141.23(k) is not incorporated by reference.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 E.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\n40 CFR 141.24(f)(17), 141.24(f)(20), and 141.24(h)(19) are not incorporated by reference.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 F.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\n40 CFR 141.25: the following text replaces the text of 40 CFR 141.25(a) and (\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 b): \\'93\\loch\\f0 \r\nAnalysis for the following contaminants shall be conducted to determine compliance with 40 CFR 141.66 (radioactivity) using analytical methods approved by EPA and the Arizona Department of Health Services:\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s62\\qj \\fi-360\\li720\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx720\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin720\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 1.\\tab Naturally occurring contaminants: gross al\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 pha and beta, gross alpha, radium 226, radium 228, and uranium.\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 2.\\tab \\hich\\f0 Man-made contaminants: radioactive cesium, radioactive iodine, radioactive strontium 89, 90, tritium, and gamma emitters.\\'94\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s59\\qj \\fi-360\\li360\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx360\\tx720\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin360\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 G.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 40 CFR 141.27, alternate analytical techniques, is not incorpor\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 ated by reference; the following text is substituted in its place: \\'93\\loch\\f0 \r\n\\hich\\f0 The use of an alternate analytical technique approved by EPA and the Arizona Department of Health Services shall not decrease the frequency of monitoring required by this Chapter.\\'94\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 H.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 40 C\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 FR 141.28:\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s62\\qj \\fi-360\\li720\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx720\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin720\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 1.\\tab \\hich\\f0 In 40 CFR 141.28(a), the term \\'93\\loch\\f0 \r\n\\hich\\f0 State\\'94\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0  is changed to \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 Arizona Department of Health Services.\\'94\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 2.\\tab \\hich\\f0 In 40 CFR 141.28(b), the term \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 State\\'94\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0  is changed to \\'93\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 \r\nArizona Department of Health Services or Arizona Department of Environmental Quality.\\'94\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 3.\\tab \\hich\\f0 A new subsection (c) is added: \\'93\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 A laboratory that performs drinking water analysis in Arizona shall be certified by EPA or the Arizona Department of Health Services.\\'94\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s34\\qc \\li0\\ri0\\sb100\\sl200\\slmult0\\keepn\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs