\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 C.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 In order to demonstrate compliance with \r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 the requirements of this Chapter:\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s62\\qj \\fi-360\\li720\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx720\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin720\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 1.\\tab \r\nPublic water systems shall use analytical methods approved by EPA and the Arizona Department of Health Services for monitoring under this Chapter; and\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 2.\\tab Analyses of drinking water samples shall be conducted by laborato\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 ries that have been certified by EPA or the Arizona Department of Health Services.\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s59\\qj \\fi-360\\li360\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx360\\tx720\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin360\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 D.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 A party approved by the Department shall measure daily chlorite samples at the entrance to the distribution system.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 E.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 A public water system may measure residual disinfec\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 tant concentrations for chlorine, chloramines, and chlorine dioxide by using N,N-diethyl-p-phenylenediamine (DPD) colorimetric test kits. A party approved by the Department shall measure residual disinfectant concentration.\r\n\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s34\\qc \\li0\\ri0\\sb100\\sl200\\slmult0\\keepn\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Historical Note\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s35\\qc \\fi-360\\li360\\ri360\\sa100\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin360\\lin360\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Former Section R\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\n9-20-519 repealed, new Section R9-20-519 adopted effective November 1, 1979 (Supp. 79-6). Former Section R9-20-519 amended, renumbered as Section R9-20-514, then renumbered as Section R18-4-114 effective October 23, 1987 (Supp. 87-4). R18-4-114 recodified\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0  \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nto R18-5-114 (Supp. 95-2). New Section adopted effective April 28, 1995 (Supp. 95-2). Section R18-4-114 renumbered to R18-4-202; new Section made by final rulemaking at 14 A.A.R. 2978, effective August 30, 2008 (Supp. 08-3).\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s15\\qj 