fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 A.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 A public water system that serves 10,000 or fewer persons sh\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nall participate in the monitoring assistance program. Within 60 days after receiving notice of participation in the monitoring assistance program from the Department, a public water system that determines that it serves more than 10,000 persons shall subs\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 t\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nantiate its determination by submitting to the Department the portion of the most recent census provided by the Arizona Department of Economic Security, Research Administration, Population Statistics Unit that supports the public water system\\hich\\f0 \r\n\\rquote \\loch\\f0 s determinat\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 i\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 on.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 B.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nA public water system that is not obligated to participate in the monitoring assistance program may elect to participate in the monitoring assistance program if the owner of the public water system: \r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s62\\qj \\fi-360\\li720\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx720\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin720\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 1.\\tab Notifies the Department in writing of the publ\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 ic water system\\hich\\f0 \\rquote \\loch\\f0 s intention to participate in the monitoring assistance program,\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 2.\\tab Agrees to participate in the monitoring assistance program for a minimum of three years, and\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 3.\\tab Pays the fees required by R18-4-304. Subject to payment of the required fees\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 , the public water system\\hich\\f0 \\rquote \\loch\\f0 \r\ns participation shall begin at the start of the next full calendar year of a compliance period.\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s34\\qc \\li0\\ri0\\sb100\\sl200\\slmult0\\keepn\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Historical Note\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s35\\qc \\fi-360\\li360\\ri360\\sa100\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin360\\lin360\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nAdopted effective April 28, 1995 (Supp. 95-2). Amended by final rulemaking at 8 A.A.R. 3046, effective May 1, 2002 (Su\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\npp. 02-3). Section R18-4-301 repealed; new Section renumbered from R18-4-224 and amended by final rulemaking at 14 A.A.R. 2978, effective August 30, 2008 (Supp. 08-3).\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s15\\qj \\li0\\ri0\\sb120\\sl200\\slmult0\\nowidctlpar\\tx1180\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 R18-4-301.01.\\tab  \\tab Renumbered\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s34\\qc \\li0\\ri0\\sb100\\sl200\\slmult0\\keepn\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Historical Note\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s35\\qc \\fi-360\\li360\\ri360\\sa100\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin360\\lin360\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 New Section adopted by final rulemaking at 5 \r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nA.A.R. 1686, effective April 19, 1999 (Supp. 99-2). Amended by final rulemaking at 8 A.A.R. 973, effective February 19, 2002 (Supp. 02-1). Section R18-4-301.01 renumbered to R18-4-212 by final rulemaking at 14 A.A.R. 2978, effective August 30, 2008 (Supp.\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0  \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 08-3)\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s15\\qj \\li0\\ri0\\sb120\\sl200\\slmult0\\nowidctlpar\\tx1180\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Table 1.\\tab Renumbered\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s34\\qc \\li0\\ri0\\sb100\\sl200\\slmult0\\keepn\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Historical Note\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s35\\qc \\fi-360\\li360\\ri360\\sa100\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin360\\lin360\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\n New Table made by final rulemaking at 8 A.A.R. 973, effective February 19, 2002 (Supp. 02-1). Table 1 following R18-4-301.01 renumbered to R18-4-212, Table 1 by final rulemaking at 14 A.A.R. 2978, effective August\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\n 30, 2008 (Supp. 08-3).\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s15\\qj \\li0\\ri0\\sb120\\sl200\\slmult0\\nowidctlpar\\tx1180\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 R18-4-301.02.\\tab \\tab Repealed\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s34\\qc \\li0\\ri0\\sb100\\sl200\\slmult0\\keepn\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Historical Note\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s35\\qc \\fi-360\\li360\\ri360\\sa100\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin360\\lin360\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nNew Section made by final rulemaking at 8 A.A.R. 3046, effective May 1, 2002 (Supp. 02-3). Section R18-4-301.02 and Tables 1 and 2 repealed by final rulemaking at 14 A.A.R. 2978, effective Aug\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 ust 30, 2008 (Supp. 08-3).\r\n\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s15\\qj \\li0\\ri0\\sb120\\sl200\\slmult0\\nowidctlpar\\tx1180\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 R18-4-302.\\tab Contractor Responsibilities\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s59\\qj \\fi-360\\li360\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx360\\tx720\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin360\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 A.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nUnder the monitoring assistance program, a contractor is authorized to collect, transport, analyze, and report water samples on behalf of a participating public water system. The contractor or a party designated by the contractor shall conduct baseline mo\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nitoring for all chemicals for which the system is required to monitor under this Chapter, except for copper, lead, disinfection byproducts, and microbiological contaminants, which remain the responsibility of the public water system. Baseline monitoring i\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\ncludes routine monitoring for contaminants included in the monitoring assistance program. Baseline monitoring does not include increased monitoring required by this Chapter when the results of baseline monitoring indicate the presence of a contaminant at \r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 a\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0  level that requires increased monitoring by a participating public water system.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 B.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nA contractor shall deliver copies of monitoring analysis results to the public water system and to the Department.\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s34\\qc \\li0\\ri0\\sb100\\sl200\\slmult0\\keepn\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Historical Note\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s35\\qc \\fi-360\\li360\\ri360\\sa100\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin360\\lin360\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Adopted effective April 28, 1995 (Supp. \r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\n95-2). Amended effective June 3, 1998 (Supp. 98-3). Amended by final rulemaking at 8 A.A.R. 3046, effective May 1, 2002 (Supp. 02-3). Section R18-4-302 repealed; new Section made by final rulemaking at 14 A.A.R. 2978, effective August 30, 2008 (Supp. 08-3\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 ).\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s15\\qj \\li0\\ri0\\sb120\\sl200\\slmult0\\nowidctlpar\\tx1180\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 R18-4-303.\\tab Public Water System Responsibilities\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s59\\qj \\fi-360\\li360\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx360\\tx720\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin360\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 A.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nAlthough a contractor performs baseline monitoring when a public water system participates in the monitoring assistance program, the public water system remains legally responsible for compliance with al\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nl other requirements of this Chapter.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 B.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nThe legal owner of a public water system participating in the monitoring assistance program shall notify the Department by July 1 of each year of:\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s62\\qj \\fi-360\\li720\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx720\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin720\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 1.\\tab The legal owner\\hich\\f0 \\rquote \\loch\\f0 \r\ns name, current mailing address, and phone number\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 ;\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 2.\\tab The population currently served by the public water system;\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 3.\\tab The public water system identification number; and\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 4.\\tab The number of meters and service connections currently in the public water system.\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s59\\qj \\fi-360\\li360\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx360\\tx720\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin360\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 C.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 A public water system that participates in the m\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 onitoring assistance program shall not deny a contractor access to or restrict a contractor\\hich\\f0 \\rquote \r\n\\loch\\f0 s access to the public water system or prevent a contractor from collecting a sample covered under the monitoring assistance program.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 D.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Direct reporting. A public \r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 water system may contract with a laboratory or another agent to report monitoring results to the Department, but the public water system remains legally responsible for compliance with reporting requirements.\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s34\\qc \\li0\\ri0\\sb100\\sl200\\slmult0\\keepn\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Historical Note\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s35\\qc \\fi-360\\li360\\ri360\\sa100\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin360\\lin360\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Adopted effective April 28, 199\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\n5 (Supp. 95-2). Amended effective June 3, 1998 (Supp. 98-3). Amended by final rulemaking at 8 A.A.R. 3046, effective May 1, 2002 (Supp. 02-3). Section R18-4-303 repealed; new Section made by final rulemaking at 14 A.A.R. 2978, effective August 30, 2008 (S\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 u\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 pp. 08-3).\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s15\\qj \\li0\\ri0\\sb120\\sl200\\slmult0\\nowidctlpar\\tx1180\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 R18-4-304.\\tab Fees for the Monitoring Assistance Program\r\n\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s59\\qj \\fi-360\\li360\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx360\\tx720\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin360\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 A.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 The Department shall assess, and a public water system participating in the monitoring assistance program shall pay, the following annual fees, subject to adjustments referenced in subsect\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 ion (B):\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s62\\qj \\fi-360\\li720\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx720\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin720\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 1.\\tab An annual fee of $250, and\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 2.\\tab A unit fee of $2.57 per meter or service connection.\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s59\\qj \\fi-360\\li360\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx360\\tx720\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin360\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 B.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 If the monitoring assistance fund has a surplus after execution of the previous year\\hich\\f0 \\rquote \\loch\\f0 s contract, any surplus in excess of $200,000 in any year shall be used t\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\no reduce future fees for public water systems that paid annual fees in the previous compliance period, in a manner consistent with the program invoicing system. In the first compliance period that a public water system participates in the monitoring assis\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 t\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nance program, the public water system shall pay the full amount of annual fees due under this Section, and is not entitled to a fee reduction resulting from a surplus in the monitoring assistance fund from a prior compliance period.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 C.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 If a public water sy\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nstem serving 10,000 or fewer persons at the beginning of a compliance period increases service during the compliance period so that the public water system serves more than 10,000 persons annually, the public water system may elect to cease participation \r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 i\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 n the monitoring assistance program under the following conditions:\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s62\\qj \\fi-360\\li720\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx720\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin720\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 1.\\tab \r\nIf the monitoring assistance program has already conducted monitoring for the public water system during the compliance period, the public water system shall remain in the monitoring as\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nsistance program, and pay annual fees, for the remainder of the compliance period.\r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 2.\\tab If the monitoring assistance program has not conducted monitoring for the public water system during the compliance period, the public water system may cease participatin\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\ng in the monitoring assistance program, and if so, the Department shall refund any monitoring fees paid by the public water system during the compliance period.\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s34\\qc \\li0\\ri0\\sb100\\sl200\\slmult0\\keepn\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Historical Note\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s35\\qc \\fi-360\\li360\\ri360\\sa100\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin360\\lin360\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nAdopted effective April 28, 1995 (Supp. 95-2). Section R18-4-304 repealed; new \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Section renumbered from R18-4-225 and amended by final rulemaking at 14 A.A.R. 2978, effective August 30, 2008 (Supp. 08-3).\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s15\\qj \\li0\\ri0\\sb120\\sl200\\slmult0\\nowidctlpar\\tx1180\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 R18-4-305.\\tab Collection and Payment of Fees\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s59\\qj \\fi-360\\li360\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx360\\tx720\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin360\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 A.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 The Department shall annually mail an invoice for fees to the legal owner of a public \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nwater system participating in the monitoring assistance program. The owner of the public water system shall pay the invoiced amount to the Department, at the address listed on the invoice, by the due date indicated on the invoice.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 B.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 The Department shall m\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nake refunds or billing corrections if a public water system demonstrates an error in the amount billed. The owner of a public water system shall send a written request for a refund or correction to the Department, at the address on the invoice, within 90 \r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 d\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 ays of the invoice date.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 C.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nThe Department may verify the number of meters and service connections of a participating public water system.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 D.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nThe Department shall not waive fees prescribed by R18-4-304.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 E.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\tab \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \\hich\\f0 \r\nThe owner of a public water system that fails to pay fees assessed by the Department in a timely manner shall be subject to the penalties listed in A.R.S. \\'a7\\loch\\f0  49-354. Failure to notify the Depar\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 tment of the owner\r\n\\hich\\f0 \\rquote \\loch\\f0 s current mailing address does not relieve the owner of a public water system from liability for penalties.\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s34\\qc \\li0\\ri0\\sb100\\sl200\\slmult0\\keepn\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Historical Note\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s35\\qc \\fi-360\\li360\\ri360\\sa100\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin360\\lin360\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex98\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nAdopted effective April 28, 1995 (Supp. 95-2). Section R18-4-305 renumbered to R18-4-306 by final rulemaking at 8\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0  A.A.R. 973, effective February 19, 2002 (Supp. 02-1). New Section R18-4-305 }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 renumbered from R18-4-226 and amended by final rulemaking at 14 A.A.R. 2978, effective August 30, 2008 (Supp. 08-3).\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s15\\qj \\li0\\ri0\\sb120\\sl200\\slmult0\\nowidctlpar\\tx1180\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 R18-4-306.\\tab Repealed\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s3