746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nTest 3: Are the proposed rates reasonable compared to the median household income of the area to be served?\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s64\\qj \\fi-360\\li720\\ri0\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\tx720\\tx1080\\tx1440\\tx1800\\tx2160\\tx2520\\tx2880\\tx3240\\tx3600\\tx3960\\tx4320\\tx4680\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin720\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 The following measurement shall be:\r\n\\par \r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Average Annual Rates < Median Household I\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 ncome* x 2.5%.\r\n\\par \r\n\\par \r\n\\par \r\n\\par \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 *\\tab \r\nThe sources of median household income data include the most recent United States Census Bureau (USCB) data collected by the Department or generated by an impartial third party experienced in collecting income data and supplied to the D\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nepartment by the applicant seeking viability determinations. Acceptable sources of income data, other than USCB data include feasibility studies, engineering reports, market studies, income surveys, or another source or collection methodology approved by \r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 t\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 he Department.\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s55\\qc \\li0\\ri0\\sb100\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 \r\n{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 Historical Note\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s110\\qc \\fi-360\\li360\\ri360\\sa200\\sl200\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin360\\lin360\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 \r\nAppendix D adopted by final rulemaking effective September 23, 1999; the A.A.R. citation was not available at the time of publication and will appear in Supp. 99-4 (Supp. 99-3). Amended by final rulemaking at 5 A.A.R. 4456, e\r\n\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 ffective September 23, 1999; Test 1(e) amended to correct a manifest clerical error (Supp. 99-4).\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s37\\qc \\li0\\ri0\\sb80\\sa80\\sl180\\slmult0\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\hyphpar0\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af1\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\caps\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af1\\hich\\af1\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af1 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af1\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f1 ARTICLE 7. REPEALED\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s15\\qj \\li0\\ri0\\sb120\\sl200\\slmult0\\nowidctlpar\\tx1180\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af0 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\charscalex100\\insrsid12746246 \\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\loch\\f0 R18-4-701.\\tab Repealed\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s34\\qc \\li0\\ri0\\sb100\\sl200\\slmult0\\keepn\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\faauto\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af0\\afs18\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\fs18\\cf1\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af0\\hich\\af0\\dbch\\af31505\\charscalex0\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp